<div id="review_235902606" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/235902606" />
    <a title="Keith Akers" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1394552-keith-akers"><img alt="Keith Akers" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1217866849p2/1394552.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/235902606?book_show_action=true">Nov 15, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Keith Akers" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Keith Akers" href="/user/show/1394552-keith-akers">Keith Akers</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9781568524436" href="/book/show/3306214-hard-tack-and-coffee">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer235902606" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13718414509159798477">This was well written and entertaining, a 19th century account by a Union soldier. One warning: there are no accounts of battles here, and it is not really told in any chronological order, although the part about enlisting does come first. Rather, it is about camp life. He talks about living in tents, army food, a typical day in camp, badges, signal flags, and so forth. There&apos;s even a chapter on the army mule. So if you want to get a sense of what it was really like in the Army during the Civil </span>
  <span id="freeText13718414509159798477" style="display:none">This was well written and entertaining, a 19th century account by a Union soldier. One warning: there are no accounts of battles here, and it is not really told in any chronological order, although the part about enlisting does come first. Rather, it is about camp life. He talks about living in tents, army food, a typical day in camp, badges, signal flags, and so forth. There's even a chapter on the army mule. So if you want to get a sense of what it was really like in the Army during the Civil War, this is an excellent account.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="13718414509159798477" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


