<div id="review_3862863055" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3862863055" />
    <a title="Gerald Hickman" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/127827768-gerald-hickman"><img alt="Gerald Hickman" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3862863055?book_show_action=true">Mar 06, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gerald Hickman" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gerald Hickman" href="/user/show/127827768-gerald-hickman">Gerald Hickman</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3862863055" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1643417228428768405">This is an easy reading book filled with mild humor. It does not deal with battles from the Civil War but about everyday life as a Union soldier. How did the Army get the supplies to feed the troops and how did they get them to the front.? <br/><br/>Includes stories about mules and horses that were so important to the movement and wintering camps of the Union Army. Why was the mule not a good animals for the Cavalry? And many other aspects of camp life and all aspects of being a Union Soldier. Spys and sp</span>
  <span id="freeText1643417228428768405" style="display:none">This is an easy reading book filled with mild humor. It does not deal with battles from the Civil War but about everyday life as a Union soldier. How did the Army get the supplies to feed the troops and how did they get them to the front.? <br /><br />Includes stories about mules and horses that were so important to the movement and wintering camps of the Union Army. Why was the mule not a good animals for the Cavalry? And many other aspects of camp life and all aspects of being a Union Soldier. Spys and spying are covered. The many types of details "enjoyed" by the soldiers around camp and on the march are mentioned. <br /><br /><br />And most important was how to cook the coffee and soften the hard tack and cook all the various foods on the Army's menu. How the soldiers helped out by foraging for extra variety for the menu.<br /><br />This is as good a read now as it was when it was a best seller in the 1880' when it first came out.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1643417228428768405" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


