<div id="review_787683677" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/787683677" />
    <a title="Nancy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1690005-nancy"><img alt="Nancy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1245807338p2/1690005.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/787683677?book_show_action=true">Dec 11, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nancy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nancy" href="/user/show/1690005-nancy">Nancy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1690005-nancy?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1690005-nancy?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1690005-nancy?shelf=memoir">memoir</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1690005-nancy?shelf=civil-war">civil-war</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer787683677" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7089028137613919664"> John Billings was a veteran of the American Civil War, but one of the best things about his book is he keeps himself mostly out of it.<br/> This is an eyewitness account of Army life from what they ate while in camp to how they organized those camps and to what happened when they began to move again. <br/> There is everything here from how they handled their comrades wounded in battle to how they punished, officially and unofficially, those who were out of line in camp. There is a sampling of bugle calls</span>
  <span id="freeText7089028137613919664" style="display:none"> John Billings was a veteran of the American Civil War, but one of the best things about his book is he keeps himself mostly out of it.<br /> This is an eyewitness account of Army life from what they ate while in camp to how they organized those camps and to what happened when they began to move again. <br /> There is everything here from how they handled their comrades wounded in battle to how they punished, officially and unofficially, those who were out of line in camp. There is a sampling of bugle calls so the reader may try some of them to hear how each sounded and in everything from dinner, to assembly and to retreat and taps.<br /> This was also another of the read aloud books my husband and I have been reading lately. This book is for anyone interested in a more realistic life of a soldier during the Civil War as opposed to the movie versions. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7089028137613919664" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


