<div id="review_2439943106" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2439943106" />
    <a title="Bobsie67" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1102847-bobsie67"><img alt="Bobsie67" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1214838737p2/1102847.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2439943106?book_show_action=true">Jul 04, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bobsie67" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bobsie67" href="/user/show/1102847-bobsie67">Bobsie67</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/39687994-hard-tack-and-coffee">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1102847-bobsie67?shelf=biography">biography</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1102847-bobsie67?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1102847-bobsie67?shelf=american-civil-war">american-civil-war</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2439943106" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8605263137693942368">Lost of details about the daily life of the Union soldier, as well as some insights into their feelings about the war, their fellow soldiers, and their military and political leaders. Some details really needed pictures--what does a Silbey tent look like, what did various patches look like, what did battle flags look like. The authors descriptions are good, but as they say, a picture is worth a thousand words. The author is at his best when he has a story to tell about the soldier&apos;s condition, a</span>
  <span id="freeText8605263137693942368" style="display:none">Lost of details about the daily life of the Union soldier, as well as some insights into their feelings about the war, their fellow soldiers, and their military and political leaders. Some details really needed pictures--what does a Silbey tent look like, what did various patches look like, what did battle flags look like. The authors descriptions are good, but as they say, a picture is worth a thousand words. The author is at his best when he has a story to tell about the soldier's condition, and at his worst when resorting to the listing of details. Must read for the true student of the Civil War since it is indeed a first-hand account of a Union soldier's rather monotonous (and sometimes rather hard) daily life.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8605263137693942368" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


