<div id="review_46161256" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/46161256" />
    <a title="Jeff Lawrence" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2018805-jeff-lawrence"><img alt="Jeff Lawrence" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/46161256?book_show_action=true">Feb 12, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeff Lawrence" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeff Lawrence" href="/user/show/2018805-jeff-lawrence">Jeff Lawrence</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer46161256" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2560710533401070376">What Company Aytch is for the Confederates, Hardtack and Coffee is for the Union boys-- an accounting of the day-to-day life of the common soldier. Unlike Company Aytch, which is woven more like a narrative, H&amp;C is written like a grandfather telling random tales of his role in the war to his grandchild; broken up and mixed around in a jambalaya of information that is as fun to read as it can be bizarre to modern audiences.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

